<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
<i>We all come from the sea,</i>

00:54.321 --> 00:57.056
but we are not all of the sea.

01:01.628 --> 01:05.798
<i>Those of us who are,</i>
<i>we children of the tides,</i>

01:05.800 --> 01:09.268
<i>must return to it</i>
<i>again and again.</i>

01:11.571 --> 01:14.573
♪♪♪

01:33.293 --> 01:36.662
<font color="#808080">BOY:</font> Four a thousand.
Five a thousand.

01:36.664 --> 01:40.265
Six a thousand.
Seven a thousand.

01:40.267 --> 01:41.867
Eight a thousand.

01:41.869 --> 01:43.268
Nine a thousand.

01:44.471 --> 01:48.674
One a thousand.
Two a thousand.

01:48.676 --> 01:51.777
Three a thousand.
Four a thousand.

01:51.779 --> 01:53.178
Five a thousand.

01:53.180 --> 01:55.314
Six a thousand.

01:55.316 --> 01:57.349
Seven a thousand.
Eight a thousand.

01:57.351 --> 01:58.851
The ball! Go over there!

01:58.853 --> 02:00.686
Pick it up, pick it up,
pick it up.

02:00.688 --> 02:02.521
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> Ten a thousand.<font color="#808080">
KIM:</font> Come on!

02:02.523 --> 02:05.290
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Eleven a thousand.

02:05.292 --> 02:07.426
Come on, Jay, let's go!
We're gonna get wet.

02:07.428 --> 02:11.396
Man, did you see that?
It's building!

02:11.398 --> 02:13.832
That was the longest one yet.

02:13.834 --> 02:17.469
One a thousand.
Two a thousand.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.872
Oh.
Three a thousand.

02:19.874 --> 02:21.373
Four a thousand.

02:21.375 --> 02:23.142
Five...
Sophie, no!

02:25.345 --> 02:28.147
♪♪♪

02:32.285 --> 02:34.353
Jay, no! Look out!

02:37.891 --> 02:39.491
Jay!

02:39.493 --> 02:39.993
♪♪♪

02:43.597 --> 02:45.597
<font color="#D900D9">(JAY COUGHING)</font>

02:48.635 --> 02:50.702
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

03:00.780 --> 03:03.682
♪♪♪

03:33.546 --> 03:35.714
<font color="#D900D9">(SOPHIE BARKING)</font>

03:44.691 --> 03:46.892
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> Oh, yeah, you're
smiling now, big shot.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.594
But if I hadn't
paddled around the Point

03:48.596 --> 03:50.229
at that exact moment...

03:50.231 --> 03:52.297
It's a miracle,
that's what it is.

03:52.299 --> 03:54.700
And I don't believe in miracles.
How old are you?

03:54.702 --> 03:57.636
What, six, seven?
Eight.

03:57.638 --> 03:59.471
And three quarters, sir.

03:59.473 --> 04:02.241
Well, you just used up your
entire allotment of dumb luck.

04:02.243 --> 04:04.576
Here's a novel idea.

04:04.578 --> 04:07.446
On your next little date,
why don't you go to the arcade?

04:07.448 --> 04:09.314
Or pee-wee golfing.

04:09.316 --> 04:11.817
Or something that doesn't
involve getting you killed.

04:11.819 --> 04:13.852
Because he likes to time
the waves.

04:13.854 --> 04:16.721
Shh.<font color="#808080">
KIM:</font> What? You do.

04:16.724 --> 04:18.322
What do you mean,
time the waves?

04:19.892 --> 04:23.862
Um, to see if the swell
is building or dropping.

04:23.864 --> 04:26.298
The more seconds between them

04:26.300 --> 04:29.668
each wave in a set,
it means it's getting bigger.

04:29.670 --> 04:31.570
Who taught you that?

04:31.572 --> 04:33.372
Nobody, sir.

04:33.374 --> 04:35.474
Just figured it out.

04:35.476 --> 04:38.377
You just figured that out
on your own?

04:40.813 --> 04:42.047
Okay.

04:42.049 --> 04:45.050
♪♪♪

04:52.625 --> 04:54.459
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Thanks. Bye.

04:54.461 --> 04:56.061
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> Bye. Okay.<font color="#808080">
KIM:</font> Bye.

04:56.063 --> 04:57.896
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> Go straight
inside, all right?

04:59.799 --> 05:01.033
Close the door.

05:12.545 --> 05:13.945
What now?

05:13.947 --> 05:16.415
How big you reckon
that wave was, sir?

05:16.417 --> 05:18.050
It's a small world, kid,

05:18.052 --> 05:20.986
but how they gauge the size
of waves, well, that differs

05:20.988 --> 05:24.423
from place to place,
so, hard to say.

05:24.425 --> 05:26.792
So it might be bigger
somewhere else?

05:29.395 --> 05:32.531
Look, it was definitely
big enough, okay?

05:45.345 --> 05:48.347
Like I said, kid, small world.

05:51.651 --> 05:54.486
I appreciate you
saving Sophie, Jay.

05:54.488 --> 05:57.489
One of the bravest things
I've ever seen.

06:01.027 --> 06:03.462
<font color="#D900D9">(BABY CRYING)</font>

06:12.905 --> 06:14.906
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Mom?

06:19.612 --> 06:21.847
♪♪♪

06:38.631 --> 06:39.831
Mom?

06:44.771 --> 06:47.806
♪♪♪

06:49.876 --> 06:51.877
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS)</font>

06:55.982 --> 06:59.184
Hi, baby.

06:59.186 --> 07:01.987
Unh. Sorry,
Mama's not feeling so good.

07:04.991 --> 07:09.461
Don't worry,
Dad will change his mind.

07:11.464 --> 07:13.965
There are hot dogs
in the fridge.

07:22.842 --> 07:25.510
♪♪♪

07:57.210 --> 07:58.810
Hey.

08:00.213 --> 08:02.013
Hey.
Need a hand?

08:02.015 --> 08:04.850
Hey. What with,
the coffee or the cupboard?

08:04.852 --> 08:07.619
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

08:07.621 --> 08:11.189
Uh, you just missed
Roque again.

08:11.191 --> 08:14.025
Just put her down.

08:14.027 --> 08:16.194
Ahem. Yeah.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.029
I had to help
a friend out after work.

08:18.031 --> 08:20.098
Mm-hm.

08:20.100 --> 08:22.567
I'll go in,
I'll give her a kiss.

08:25.571 --> 08:27.906
Kiss would be nice.

08:27.908 --> 08:31.176
Conversation every once
in a while, maybe nicer.

08:36.249 --> 08:38.650
<font color="#808080">CHRISTY:</font>
Time to wake up, Jay.

08:41.554 --> 08:42.754
Okay.

08:42.756 --> 08:43.989
How do I look?

08:43.991 --> 08:45.924
You look awesome.

08:47.193 --> 08:50.595
I have an interview at Sears.

08:50.597 --> 08:52.597
So, I'm coming home at 12:00

08:52.599 --> 08:53.999
and we are going
to get school supplies.

08:54.001 --> 08:55.634
Good luck.

08:55.636 --> 08:57.235
Thank you.

08:57.237 --> 08:59.237
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

09:06.946 --> 09:08.980
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

09:20.259 --> 09:22.260
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

09:25.565 --> 09:28.266
♪♪♪

09:57.129 --> 09:58.597
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

10:06.706 --> 10:08.273
Excuse me. Ma'am?

10:08.275 --> 10:10.342
Hi.
Your husband home?

10:10.344 --> 10:13.078
Uh, well,
depends on who's asking.

10:13.080 --> 10:15.280
I'm Jay Moriarty, ma'am.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.682
He saved my life
down at Three Mile yesterday.

10:17.684 --> 10:19.918
Oh, sweetie, I'm sorry,
I think you're mistaken

10:19.920 --> 10:22.654
because Frosty was up in Scott's
Valley laying roof yesterday.

10:22.656 --> 10:25.924
No, ma'am. He was surfing
the exact same time

10:25.926 --> 10:27.759
I used up my allotment
of dumb luck.

10:29.061 --> 10:30.395
Is that so?

10:30.397 --> 10:34.099
Frosty is actually
down at The Point right now

10:34.101 --> 10:37.936
but is there anything that I can
help you with, Jay Moriarty?

10:37.938 --> 10:43.875
Well, I seem to be missing parts
on the bottom of my board.

10:47.380 --> 10:48.847
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font>
Okay.

10:48.849 --> 10:50.849
Fins, fins, fins.

10:53.219 --> 10:55.720
Where does he keep them? Oh.<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> Wow.

10:59.191 --> 11:01.693
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font>
They call that thing a gun.

11:01.695 --> 11:03.094
<font color="#D900D9">(BRENDA CHUCKLES)</font>

11:03.096 --> 11:05.130
It's for riding
the really big monsters.

11:05.132 --> 11:06.364
Like that.

11:07.767 --> 11:09.134
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Where is that?

11:09.136 --> 11:10.935
You should ask Frosty yourself.

11:10.937 --> 11:12.137
Thanks.

11:12.139 --> 11:15.306
♪♪♪

11:18.077 --> 11:19.377
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

11:21.147 --> 11:23.314
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

11:43.202 --> 11:45.370
Beat it, little trash.

12:06.225 --> 12:06.725
♪♪♪

12:52.972 --> 12:54.372
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

13:00.112 --> 13:02.213
♪♪♪

13:18.998 --> 13:22.066
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS THEN COUGHING)</font>

13:23.502 --> 13:26.571
Blondie, what are you doing?

13:28.574 --> 13:30.408
Hey, man, you got to go in.

13:30.410 --> 13:31.876
You're bleeding.

13:31.878 --> 13:35.146
I can't.
Not until I get up.

13:35.148 --> 13:38.850
Dude, believe me, nobody
gets up their first time.

13:38.852 --> 13:40.985
Okay, okay.
I'm only doing this

13:40.987 --> 13:42.587
because you're gonna start
attracting sharks

13:42.589 --> 13:44.189
with all that blood.

13:44.191 --> 13:47.158
When I say "now,"
you paddle as hard as you can

13:47.160 --> 13:49.260
towards shore, you got it?

13:49.262 --> 13:51.429
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> Now?
No.

13:52.865 --> 13:54.866
Now?
No.

13:56.302 --> 13:58.436
Now?
Yeah! Paddle, paddle, paddle.

13:58.438 --> 14:00.572
<font color="#D900D9">(SPONGE'S "PLOWED" PLAYING)</font>

14:19.625 --> 14:24.429
<i>♪ Will I wake up?</i>
<i>Some dream I made up? ♪</i>

14:24.431 --> 14:30.568
<i>♪ No, I guess it's reality</i>

14:32.371 --> 14:37.008
<i>♪ What will change us?</i>
<i>Or will we mess up ♪</i>

14:37.010 --> 14:42.046
<i>♪ Our only chance</i>
<i>To connect with a dream? ♪</i>

14:45.084 --> 14:46.985
<i>♪ Say a prayer for me</i>

14:46.987 --> 14:49.587
<i>♪ Say a prayer for me</i>

14:49.589 --> 14:54.092
<i>♪ Say a prayer for me</i>
<i>For me, for me ♪</i>

14:54.094 --> 14:56.461
<i>♪ Say a prayer for me</i>

14:56.463 --> 14:58.396
<i>♪ Say a prayer for me</i>

14:58.398 --> 15:03.668
<i>♪ I'm buried by the sound</i>

15:10.109 --> 15:12.477
Hey, paddle.
Paddle, paddle, paddle! Now!

15:12.479 --> 15:14.512
Go, go, go!

15:14.514 --> 15:16.514
Yeah!

15:16.516 --> 15:19.317
You stealing a page out
of my playbook there?

15:19.319 --> 15:20.618
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

15:20.620 --> 15:22.420
Couldn't help myself, Blondie.

15:22.422 --> 15:25.223
It's always been a keeper.

15:25.225 --> 15:27.058
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHATTERING)</font>

15:28.394 --> 15:30.561
Hey, little trash.

15:30.563 --> 15:33.498
Got a question for you.
Yeah.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.466
What exactly are you
trying to compensate for

15:35.468 --> 15:37.702
with this long board
of yours? Huh?

15:37.704 --> 15:41.272
I was about to ask you
the same thing about that bat.

15:44.009 --> 15:46.411
Y'all come back now, you hear?
<font color="#D900D9">(BAT CLANGS)</font>

15:46.413 --> 15:49.013
<font color="#D900D9">(MICKY WOLF'S "HOMETOWN REGGAE"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)</font>

15:49.015 --> 15:50.348
<font color="#808080">BOY 1:</font>
Come on, let's go!

15:50.350 --> 15:51.549
Okay, okay, we're coming.

15:51.551 --> 15:53.251
<font color="#808080">BOY 1:</font>
Sometime today, please.

15:53.253 --> 15:55.653
<font color="#D900D9">(BOY 2 & GIRL
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

15:55.655 --> 15:57.388
Hey, Kim.

15:57.390 --> 15:59.691
Hi! How was it out there?

15:59.693 --> 16:01.526
Good. Feels like
the swell is building.

16:01.528 --> 16:04.295
Yeah? Did you time it?

16:04.297 --> 16:06.130
<font color="#808080">BOY 1:</font>
Kimmy, come on, we got to go.

16:06.132 --> 16:09.200
Um, all right, well,
maybe I'll see you out there.

16:09.202 --> 16:12.403
Later. Whoo!

16:17.443 --> 16:19.043
Let her be, dude.

16:19.045 --> 16:21.579
She's too old for you.

16:21.581 --> 16:25.350
<font color="#808080">CHRISTY:</font> Get out! Get
out of my house! Aah!

16:25.352 --> 16:27.151
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Get down!<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> Mom!

16:27.153 --> 16:28.686
<font color="#808080">ELI:</font> And you stay down there!
I'm tired of this!

16:28.688 --> 16:31.222
Get off me! Okay?<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> Mom!

16:31.224 --> 16:32.457
<font color="#808080">ELI:</font>
I'm not going anywhere!

16:32.459 --> 16:33.725
Jay.

16:33.727 --> 16:36.327
Easy, kid.
This is about back rent!

16:36.329 --> 16:38.363
She tried grabbing me!
All I did...

16:38.365 --> 16:39.630
<font color="#808080">CHRISTY:</font>
He owes us money!

16:39.632 --> 16:41.466
Get off me! Unh!

16:41.468 --> 16:43.534
No!
Take it easy, kid!

16:43.536 --> 16:44.769
<font color="#808080">CHRISTY:</font>
Jay! No!

16:44.771 --> 16:47.305
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font>
Jay! Jay, stop, stop! Jay!

16:47.307 --> 16:50.208
<font color="#D900D9">(SIREN WAILING)</font>

16:50.210 --> 16:53.144
Cops! Cops!
Just let him go! Come on!

16:54.713 --> 16:56.614
<font color="#808080">OFFICER 1:</font> Hey, hey! Break it up!
Break it up!

16:58.317 --> 17:01.185
<font color="#808080">ELI:</font>
Get off me!

17:01.187 --> 17:03.087
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

17:05.057 --> 17:07.759
<font color="#808080">OFFICER 2:</font> This is Victor-1-2.
We're on the scene.

17:07.761 --> 17:08.261
♪♪♪

17:34.520 --> 17:36.120
<font color="#D900D9">(VAN DOOR OPENS)</font>

17:37.289 --> 17:38.523
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>

17:47.132 --> 17:50.134
♪♪♪

17:56.542 --> 17:58.142
<font color="#D900D9">(VAN DOOR CLOSES)</font>

18:04.183 --> 18:06.284
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font> <i>Offshore
buoys are reporting seas</i>

18:06.286 --> 18:08.219
<i>of 25 feet at 16 seconds.</i>

18:10.856 --> 18:14.125
<i>Coming from the west</i>
<i>northwest at 295 degrees.</i>

18:14.127 --> 18:16.561
Northwest winds are forecasted
<i>at 15 to 20 knots.</i>

18:16.563 --> 18:19.564
<i>Swells are expected</i>
<i>to reach up to 28 feet</i>

18:19.566 --> 18:21.766
<i>at 17 seconds near shore.</i>

18:32.177 --> 18:34.745
♪♪♪

18:54.500 --> 18:55.833
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Morning, Frank.

18:55.835 --> 18:57.335
Careful out there, son.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.492
Hey, buddy.
What's up?

19:23.662 --> 19:26.797
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Next level out
there today, boys.

19:26.799 --> 19:28.232
Twenty-five at 16.

19:28.234 --> 19:30.768
Let's rock and roll.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.370
Right.

19:32.372 --> 19:33.704
Let's do it.

19:33.706 --> 19:37.241
♪♪♪

21:53.645 --> 21:55.913
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Yeah, Frosty!

22:04.456 --> 22:06.824
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> Now, we'll agree to
forget how you got up here,

22:06.826 --> 22:08.826
but as far as most
are concerned,

22:08.828 --> 22:11.896
that wave's a myth.
Like the Loch Ness monster.

22:11.898 --> 22:14.465
The four of us who surf there
want to keep it that way.

22:14.467 --> 22:15.666
Is that clear?

22:18.070 --> 22:20.071
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <i>Buoys reporting
swells of 28 feet</i>

22:20.073 --> 22:21.972
<i>at 17 seconds coming from...</i>

22:21.974 --> 22:23.641
<font color="#D900D9">(TURNS OFF RADIO)</font>

22:26.411 --> 22:27.678
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

22:29.715 --> 22:30.915
How big was that wave?

22:30.917 --> 22:32.817
Did you hear what I just said?

22:34.686 --> 22:36.420
Yes, sir.

22:36.422 --> 22:37.822
Loch Ness monster.

22:45.364 --> 22:46.564
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

22:51.103 --> 22:52.737
How's it going over there?

22:52.739 --> 22:55.573
Mom's not renting out
the back anymore.

22:55.575 --> 22:57.441
Means I get my own room.

22:57.443 --> 22:59.977
But I got to double-up
my shifts at Pleasure Pizza.

23:01.847 --> 23:03.047
And your father?

23:05.517 --> 23:06.917
He wrote me a letter
a few years back

23:06.919 --> 23:08.119
from his base in Panama.

23:09.921 --> 23:11.122
So what'd he say?

23:13.058 --> 23:15.459
I don't know.

23:15.461 --> 23:17.128
Never opened it.

23:21.133 --> 23:22.767
All right, well,

23:22.769 --> 23:25.569
I got to get out of here.
Got to get to work.

23:28.073 --> 23:31.776
Hey, sir, I want
to ride that wave.

23:31.778 --> 23:33.177
I want to take that drop.

23:33.179 --> 23:34.678
Not gonna happen.

23:34.680 --> 23:36.480
Why not?

23:36.482 --> 23:38.883
Because untrained boys
don't step in the ring

23:38.885 --> 23:40.851
with Mike Tyson, that's why.

23:40.853 --> 23:43.954
I can handle it.
You don't just do it.

23:43.956 --> 23:46.791
Buddy, I've been surfing
that break for 20 years.

23:46.793 --> 23:49.493
You have any idea how much
strength and know-how you need

23:49.495 --> 23:50.795
to survive a break like that?

23:50.797 --> 23:52.696
Frosty, I'm getting
stronger by the day.

23:52.698 --> 23:55.166
I'll hold my own.

23:55.168 --> 23:57.902
Stronger by the day, huh?
Yeah.

23:57.904 --> 24:00.638
Okay, give me your hand.

24:01.640 --> 24:02.973
Now resist me.

24:02.975 --> 24:04.442
Okay, that all you got?

24:04.444 --> 24:05.676
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

24:05.678 --> 24:08.212
Is that it? Is that it?

24:08.214 --> 24:11.048
Ow. Ow, ow, ow.
Okay.

24:11.050 --> 24:13.117
You ain't strong enough.

24:14.986 --> 24:17.788
Right now, I'm surfing every
single day, right? So, if I...

24:17.790 --> 24:20.157
Shut up, all right?

24:20.159 --> 24:21.926
Now, I know how good you are.

24:21.928 --> 24:23.928
I've seen you out there.

24:23.930 --> 24:27.631
You surf circles around
those other kids.

24:27.633 --> 24:30.634
But those are normal waves.

24:30.636 --> 24:32.770
Surfing normal waves
is about how you perform

24:32.772 --> 24:34.672
when everything goes right.

24:34.674 --> 24:37.942
Now, big wave surfing,
that's a different ball game.

24:37.944 --> 24:40.478
That's about how you perform
when everything goes wrong.

24:42.013 --> 24:44.682
One bump off the face
of that wave,

24:44.684 --> 24:46.517
and you're hitting the water
like concrete

24:46.519 --> 24:47.918
at 50 miles an hour.

24:47.920 --> 24:49.620
And you got a thousand tons
of water

24:49.622 --> 24:51.121
coming down on top of you.

24:51.123 --> 24:53.691
It's knocking you senseless,
ripping you apart

24:53.693 --> 24:56.827
and pushing you down to a place
that is so deep and so dark,

24:58.263 --> 25:00.231
you don't want to be there.

25:01.500 --> 25:02.967
So why do it?

25:04.569 --> 25:09.840
Hey. Come on, get out of here.
I got work to do.

25:09.842 --> 25:12.910
Train me, then.
Train me to ride it.

25:12.912 --> 25:14.211
Did you hear what I said?

25:14.213 --> 25:16.580
Go on, get.

25:26.892 --> 25:28.993
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font>
You don't get it, do you?

25:35.600 --> 25:37.701
What?

25:37.703 --> 25:41.805
There are all kinds of sons,
Frosty, you know?

25:41.807 --> 25:45.142
Some are born to you
and some just occur to you.

25:46.678 --> 25:49.246
Jay's looked up to you
his entire life.

25:49.248 --> 25:51.715
I mean, can't you see
how much he needs you?

25:51.717 --> 25:53.984
You want me to teach
him to surf that wave?

25:53.986 --> 25:56.153
He's a kid.

25:56.155 --> 25:58.088
You made me promise
I wouldn't even surf that...

25:58.090 --> 25:59.590
Yeah,
and you break that promise

25:59.592 --> 26:01.025
every chance you get.

26:01.027 --> 26:03.027
You think I don't know
where you were this morning?

26:03.029 --> 26:04.728
I heard the message
on the machine.

26:04.730 --> 26:06.230
"25 at 16"? Come on.

26:06.232 --> 26:08.132
I don't know where
you're going with this.

26:08.134 --> 26:11.201
That boy's gonna surf that wave
anyway. You know that, right?

26:11.203 --> 26:13.871
Even if he dies trying.

26:14.906 --> 26:16.907
I mean, wouldn't you?

26:20.011 --> 26:23.047
♪♪♪

26:37.162 --> 26:39.797
<font color="#D900D9">(CORNERSHOP'S "BRIMFUL OF ASHA"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)</font>

26:39.799 --> 26:41.599
<i>♪ She's the one</i>
<i>That keeps the dream alive ♪</i>

26:41.601 --> 26:45.336
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font> Okay, two Hawaiians,
two Santa Barbara,

26:45.338 --> 26:47.237
one pepperoni and one cheese.
All right.

26:47.239 --> 26:48.906
<font color="#808080">GIRL:</font>
Thank you.

26:48.908 --> 26:51.275
<i>♪ Well, it's a</i>
<i>Brimful of asha ♪</i>

26:51.277 --> 26:53.877
Dude. Dude.

26:53.879 --> 26:56.714
It goes, first sauce,
then cheese, then toppings.

26:56.716 --> 26:59.116
It's not rocket science.

26:59.118 --> 27:02.353
You all right? You haven't been
here since you got here, man.

27:02.355 --> 27:05.623
You ever see something
and you think,

27:05.625 --> 27:07.224
like, it's the reason
you were put here?

27:07.226 --> 27:08.826
I mean, like, on this earth?

27:08.828 --> 27:10.928
Sure, man.

27:10.930 --> 27:12.830
Every time I turn on <i>Baywatch.</i>

27:14.699 --> 27:16.667
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

27:16.669 --> 27:18.235
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font>
Right, keep it moving.

27:18.237 --> 27:20.971
Pleasure Pizza. Okay.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.673
Hey, Blond, I'll be right back.

27:22.675 --> 27:24.675
Hold on, hold on. Hey, dude,
where are you going now?

27:24.677 --> 27:26.810
I'll be right back.<font color="#808080">
BLOND:</font> You're killing me here!

27:26.812 --> 27:28.712
Hi, sir.

27:28.714 --> 27:30.247
Okay, here's the deal.

27:30.249 --> 27:32.116
I'm gonna train you
for one thing

27:32.118 --> 27:33.717
and for one thing only:

27:33.719 --> 27:36.020
To survive that wave.
All right?

27:36.022 --> 27:37.421
You want to know why?

27:37.423 --> 27:40.391
Because I don't want it
on my conscience.

27:40.393 --> 27:41.959
That's it.

27:41.961 --> 27:43.994
No questions, no arguing,
end of story.

27:43.996 --> 27:47.031
I teach you what you need
to know, and it's over.

27:47.033 --> 27:49.033
You got it?
Got it.

27:49.035 --> 27:52.836
Now, the reason
no one knows about this wave

27:52.838 --> 27:55.239
is because it only happens
on big northwest swells.

27:55.241 --> 27:58.676
And the window for those swells
closes in 12 weeks.

27:58.678 --> 28:00.010
So you got 12 weeks.

28:01.446 --> 28:04.915
Meet me in my shed
tomorrow morning, 6:30 a.m.

28:04.917 --> 28:06.984
Not 6:31 or 6:32.

28:12.724 --> 28:14.224
Yes! Yes! Yes!

28:22.300 --> 28:24.435
Hey. Ooh.

28:24.437 --> 28:28.172
Don't bother with that.
We're not surfing.

28:30.241 --> 28:32.443
Paddleboards.

28:32.445 --> 28:34.078
All right. Unh.

28:34.080 --> 28:37.915
A few things we need to
establish before we begin.

28:37.917 --> 28:39.183
The first,

28:40.485 --> 28:42.252
thou shalt not ding
Frosty's board

28:42.254 --> 28:43.487
or damage thy neighbor's car.

28:43.489 --> 28:46.056
Yes, sir. Sorry, sir.

28:46.058 --> 28:49.760
Second,
this little, uh, program

28:49.762 --> 28:52.796
is all about building
what I like to call

28:52.798 --> 28:57.034
the four pillars of a solid
human foundation. Understand?

28:58.136 --> 28:59.903
Yes, sir.

28:59.905 --> 29:02.206
How could you? I haven't even
told you what they are.

29:04.476 --> 29:06.510
Steady rhythm.

29:06.512 --> 29:08.011
Drive and glide.

29:18.256 --> 29:22.259
The four pillars
of the human foundation

29:22.261 --> 29:24.795
are the physical, the mental,

29:24.797 --> 29:28.031
the emotional
and the spiritual.

29:28.033 --> 29:30.100
Though I admit
to being a little bit wobbly

29:30.102 --> 29:32.102
in that department.

29:32.104 --> 29:33.937
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> I'm not sure I
understand, sir.

29:35.240 --> 29:36.540
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
You know what a thesis is?

29:36.542 --> 29:38.842
Uh, an idea.

29:38.844 --> 29:42.045
Exactly. An idea which attempts
to explain something.

29:42.047 --> 29:44.114
Lays it out to be
proved or disproved.

29:44.116 --> 29:46.116
So here's our thesis:

29:46.118 --> 29:49.520
It's 36 miles across the bay
from Santa Cruz to Monterey.

29:49.522 --> 29:52.389
The day that you can
paddle that far

29:52.391 --> 29:54.992
will be the day
you're ready to surf Mavericks.

29:54.994 --> 29:56.493
Not a moment sooner.

29:56.495 --> 29:57.895
Frosty, that's impossible.

29:57.897 --> 30:00.531
Oh, more so than you know.

30:00.533 --> 30:03.267
So the physical will represent
the sheer strength

30:03.269 --> 30:05.068
needed to make the paddle.

30:05.070 --> 30:07.271
So you're gonna be doing this
from now on, every day,

30:07.273 --> 30:08.939
12 weeks.

30:08.941 --> 30:13.177
And the mental will be tied
to your own research.

30:13.179 --> 30:15.312
The calculation
of the tides and swells,

30:15.314 --> 30:17.414
and, of course, your ability
to navigate them all.

30:20.318 --> 30:23.287
So, Monterey equals Mavericks.
Deal?

30:24.422 --> 30:27.891
Deal.
Good. All I need

30:27.893 --> 30:29.393
is for your mom
to sign me a permission slip

30:29.395 --> 30:31.161
accepting responsibility

30:31.163 --> 30:33.363
for anything that's
gonna happen along the way.

30:33.365 --> 30:35.566
Whoa. Frosty.

30:35.568 --> 30:39.169
Hey, Frosty, what if
she doesn't sign it?

30:39.171 --> 30:43.307
Deep breaths, steady rhythm.
Drive and glide.

30:43.309 --> 30:47.144
<font color="#D900D9">(MAZZY STAR'S "BLUE LIGHT"
PLAYING SOFTLY OVER SPEAKERS)</font>

30:49.614 --> 30:51.615
<font color="#D900D9">(SOPHIE WHIMPERING)</font>

30:53.051 --> 30:55.319
Hey, Sophie.
What's up, girl?

30:56.421 --> 30:57.855
Come here, Sophie.
Shh.

30:57.857 --> 30:59.923
Sophie. What are you...?

30:59.925 --> 31:02.226
What are you doing here?
My parents are asleep.

31:02.228 --> 31:04.461
Can you sign me
a permission slip

31:04.463 --> 31:07.030
with my mom's signature on it?
My handwriting blows.

31:07.032 --> 31:11.168
Hey. A permission slip?
For what?

31:11.170 --> 31:14.204
Okay, I haven't told this
to anyone

31:14.206 --> 31:16.240
so you have to promise
to keep it a secret.

31:16.242 --> 31:18.542
Okay, promise.

31:18.544 --> 31:20.944
It's Mavericks.
I mean, it's real.

31:20.946 --> 31:23.547
Maybe the biggest wave
in the world.

31:23.549 --> 31:26.383
I've seen it with my own eyes,
it's right up the coast.

31:26.385 --> 31:29.553
Frosty's gonna train me
to surf it.

31:29.555 --> 31:32.089
Mavericks?
No one believes that.

31:32.091 --> 31:34.391
I swear, it's like nothing
you've ever seen before.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.226
And if I ask my mom
for permission,

31:36.228 --> 31:38.328
it'll just give her an excuse
to act like my mom for once

31:38.330 --> 31:40.063
and she'll probably say no.

31:43.101 --> 31:46.270
You look great.
Thanks.

31:46.272 --> 31:48.138
I would've asked you at school,
but I know you don't like

31:48.140 --> 31:49.907
being seen in public
with younger men, so...

31:51.643 --> 31:53.110
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

32:01.519 --> 32:03.520
<font color="#808080">SONNY:</font>
Hey, Blondie.

32:09.627 --> 32:11.628
<font color="#D900D9">(SONNY & BLOND
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

32:18.303 --> 32:19.536
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font>
All right, fellas.

32:22.140 --> 32:25.309
Come on, race you to the pool.

32:25.311 --> 32:29.313
(THE OFFSPRING'S "COME OUT AND PLAY
<font color="#D900D9">(KEEP 'EM SEPARATED)</font>" PLAYING)

32:34.085 --> 32:35.319
<i>♪ You gotta</i>
<i>Keep 'em separated ♪</i>

32:35.321 --> 32:37.020
<font color="#808080">BELLS:</font>
Ow!

32:43.261 --> 32:46.430
Yeah! Sick!

32:52.470 --> 32:53.971
Get some!

32:56.374 --> 32:58.408
Whoo! Yeah!
Aah!

32:58.410 --> 33:01.044
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font>
Yeah, man, get up.

33:01.046 --> 33:02.713
Yeah.

33:02.715 --> 33:05.048
Hey. Hollybra's having a party
tonight. You clowns going?

33:05.050 --> 33:08.118
Yeah, sounds good to me.
Jay?

33:08.120 --> 33:09.453
No, I got school and stuff.

33:09.455 --> 33:11.588
Dude.

33:11.590 --> 33:13.390
We all got school, dude.
That's no excuse.

33:13.392 --> 33:14.758
Heard that. Haven't been
to class all week.

33:14.760 --> 33:16.593
<font color="#808080">BLOND:</font>
Yeah.

33:16.595 --> 33:21.231
The dude actually wonders why
he's a second-year sophomore!

33:21.233 --> 33:23.767
So, what kind of stuff
you got going?

33:23.769 --> 33:27.204
Just trying to make sense
of everything.

33:27.206 --> 33:29.106
We're in high school, dude.

33:29.108 --> 33:32.109
<i>♪ Man, you disrespecting me?</i>
<i>Take him out ♪</i>

33:32.111 --> 33:34.277
<i>♪ You gotta</i>
<i>Keep 'em separated ♪</i>

33:35.480 --> 33:37.681
Hey, Frosty.

33:37.683 --> 33:39.316
Hey.

33:42.754 --> 33:45.088
It's 20 to 4.

33:45.090 --> 33:46.723
You told me to be here at 4.

33:46.725 --> 33:48.492
Exactly.

33:50.061 --> 33:52.429
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> So, we ready to go?
Does it look like it?

33:55.133 --> 33:58.602
Tell you what, we'll be ready

33:58.604 --> 34:00.637
when you clean up
that driveway.

34:00.639 --> 34:04.107
That's what you get for
being 20 minutes early.

34:13.384 --> 34:15.552
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Deep breaths.

34:15.554 --> 34:19.389
You got to stretch
out those lungs.

34:19.391 --> 34:22.458
A wave like Mavericks will hold
you down for minutes at a time

34:22.460 --> 34:24.161
while it pounds you to a pulp.

34:24.163 --> 34:25.762
If you can't hold your breath

34:25.764 --> 34:28.632
for at least four minutes
under normal circumstances,

34:28.634 --> 34:30.667
then you may as well
not even paddle out.

34:41.779 --> 34:43.547
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

34:43.549 --> 34:45.382
How long was that?

34:47.552 --> 34:49.319
You know what, I'm not even
gonna acknowledge

34:49.321 --> 34:50.654
that just happened.

35:11.309 --> 35:12.642
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Hey.

35:13.845 --> 35:15.679
Where'd you find that?

35:17.582 --> 35:21.318
In the dresser that you
moved into the baby's room.

35:21.320 --> 35:26.223
Hm.
God, you're so beautiful.

35:26.225 --> 35:28.325
Mm.

35:36.234 --> 35:40.337
Look, um, I know that surfing

35:40.339 --> 35:44.241
is your passion and your life,
your escape.

35:44.243 --> 35:45.742
I get it.

35:47.478 --> 35:49.312
But I need you to
make me a promise.

35:50.515 --> 35:53.416
And I'm serious this time.

35:56.888 --> 35:59.756
That you're not gonna put
the rush of a 30-foot drop

35:59.758 --> 36:02.225
in front of the future
of your two children.

36:02.227 --> 36:03.894
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

36:11.435 --> 36:12.636
I promise.

36:14.906 --> 36:17.340
God, you're a good man.

36:19.677 --> 36:21.778
Okay.

36:21.780 --> 36:23.346
Jay's waiting for you.

36:31.956 --> 36:33.356
Mom!

36:33.358 --> 36:34.925
Mom, you got to get up
right now!

36:34.927 --> 36:36.793
You got a 6:00 shift!

36:36.795 --> 36:39.829
You're gonna lose
your job again! Mom!

36:39.831 --> 36:41.531
Oh, no.

36:43.668 --> 36:46.570
Mom, get up! Come on!
I'm getting up!

36:49.674 --> 36:51.675
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

37:19.704 --> 37:21.304
Hey.

37:22.840 --> 37:24.374
You're 11 minutes late.

37:24.376 --> 37:26.509
Yeah, sorry, Frosty.
You know, my mom...

37:26.511 --> 37:28.311
She had to write
my permission slip, so...

37:36.354 --> 37:37.821
Your mother's got
nice handwriting.

37:40.291 --> 37:41.658
She take much convincing?

37:43.995 --> 37:45.428
No.

37:45.430 --> 37:47.397
Not much.

37:48.532 --> 37:49.733
Good.

37:57.341 --> 37:58.742
That your breakfast?

37:58.744 --> 38:00.710
Hm? Yeah.

38:03.748 --> 38:05.782
You want to be an athlete,
you got to eat like one.

38:05.784 --> 38:07.317
Take this.

38:09.020 --> 38:10.487
Go on, take it.

38:10.489 --> 38:11.888
You're gonna need it
more than me.

38:13.024 --> 38:14.891
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Thanks.

38:14.893 --> 38:16.793
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font> <i>Winds out
of the south, southeast</i>

38:16.795 --> 38:19.329
<i>at 15 knots,</i>
<i>gusting to 20 knots.</i>

38:19.331 --> 38:21.398
That's the Weather Radio, huh?

38:21.400 --> 38:22.799
You use it to follow big surf?

38:22.801 --> 38:24.901
Kind of like you
timing the waves.

38:24.903 --> 38:27.003
Only this thing's
a little more accurate.

38:27.005 --> 38:28.638
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

38:28.640 --> 38:29.140
♪♪♪

38:38.382 --> 38:39.983
There's no way
to paddle out there,

38:39.985 --> 38:41.918
especially with long boards.

38:41.920 --> 38:45.555
Oh, there's a way, all right.

38:45.557 --> 38:48.358
So let's see if you're
worth your salt, chief.

38:51.796 --> 38:55.398
♪♪♪

39:36.574 --> 39:38.575
Okay, back to baking.

39:39.777 --> 39:41.845
Let's go.

39:41.847 --> 39:46.049
So you made it all of 30 yards.

39:46.051 --> 39:48.618
If you want to get out there,
you got to make it

39:48.620 --> 39:50.153
through more than half
a mile of this

39:50.155 --> 39:52.155
just to get in position
of Mavericks.

39:52.157 --> 39:55.992
So you've got to conserve
all the energy you've got.

39:56.994 --> 39:58.962
All right.

39:58.964 --> 40:01.097
Now let's take a look
at what you missed.

40:02.566 --> 40:04.868
Now, for some reason,
you decided

40:04.870 --> 40:07.971
to paddle straight out
into that mess.

40:09.440 --> 40:11.174
Now, take a look
at the rocks over there.

40:11.176 --> 40:13.877
See what's happening
with the current?

40:15.613 --> 40:17.814
It's got nowhere to go.
Nowhere to go but where?

40:21.018 --> 40:23.019
Back out?
Exactly, back out.

40:23.021 --> 40:24.954
To a waterman,

40:26.424 --> 40:28.591
it's a conveyor belt.

40:28.593 --> 40:30.160
Watch this.

40:58.522 --> 40:59.923
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
<i>So today's lesson</i>

40:59.925 --> 41:02.926
was about the power
of observation.

41:02.928 --> 41:05.662
Simple fact
is you got two choices.

41:05.664 --> 41:07.497
You can fight things head-on

41:07.499 --> 41:10.533
or you can observe
the laws of nature.

41:10.535 --> 41:12.702
Because if you
look hard enough,

41:12.704 --> 41:14.671
there's always
a way through it.

41:14.673 --> 41:17.941
Make sense?
Yes, sir.

41:17.943 --> 41:19.676
Good man.

41:19.678 --> 41:22.111
Because you're going to
write me an essay about it.

41:22.113 --> 41:26.549
Three pages,
typewritten, single-space.

41:26.551 --> 41:30.086
Devil's in the details
of whatever you observe.

41:30.088 --> 41:33.556
Time to start building
your mental pillar, chief.

41:40.931 --> 41:42.699
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Hey, Kimmy.

41:43.701 --> 41:46.135
Oh, my gosh!
Are you okay?

41:46.137 --> 41:47.570
Yeah.

41:47.572 --> 41:49.005
Oh, man.

41:49.007 --> 41:50.273
What are you doing?

41:50.275 --> 41:53.843
Uh, I just
got off work. You?

41:53.845 --> 41:56.112
Oh, um, I was just trying
to go for a swim,

41:56.114 --> 41:58.147
but I guess they close
early on Sundays.

41:58.149 --> 42:00.116
You want to go swimming
at night,

42:00.118 --> 42:01.718
you got to use
the back entrance.

42:01.720 --> 42:03.152
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

42:03.154 --> 42:05.255
Hey, this isn't so bad.

42:10.294 --> 42:15.064
Okay, so how do we get down?

42:15.066 --> 42:17.300
There's only one way I know of.

42:17.302 --> 42:19.969
What? No. Are you serious?

42:19.971 --> 42:22.238
No. Jay!

42:22.240 --> 42:23.740
<font color="#808080">BOY:</font>
Hey.

42:23.742 --> 42:27.577
I saw your bike.
You didn't tell me.

42:29.146 --> 42:32.148
So she know the rules?
No.

42:32.150 --> 42:34.150
Clear it. Clear it.
Excuse me.

42:34.152 --> 42:35.752
It's kind of like
figure skating.

42:35.754 --> 42:38.621
Points based on a combination
of style,

42:38.623 --> 42:40.790
execution and difficulty.

42:40.792 --> 42:44.027
For example, I'm going to start
with a standing one and a half.

42:44.029 --> 42:48.932
High, I repeat,
high level of difficulty.

42:48.934 --> 42:51.167
Because I got to clear
the pool deck.

42:51.169 --> 42:54.904
Hit that,
you're immediately DQ'd.

42:54.906 --> 42:56.839
No. Wait, wait, wait.
You guys aren't serious.

42:56.841 --> 42:58.207
Really? No!

42:58.209 --> 43:01.611
<font color="#D900D9">(MATTHEW SWEET'S
"GIRLFRIEND" PLAYING)</font>

43:01.613 --> 43:03.179
Oh...
Oh!

43:04.815 --> 43:06.182
And the judges say...

43:06.184 --> 43:07.884
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font> Oh, my gosh.<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> Nice one, Blondie.

43:07.886 --> 43:11.020
The only thing that can top
that is a reverse back tuck.

43:11.022 --> 43:14.023
Because of the blind entry.
No! I can't watch this.

43:14.025 --> 43:15.792
You have to.

43:15.794 --> 43:17.827
You're the only judge.

43:17.829 --> 43:19.095
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font>
No, Jay!

43:19.097 --> 43:21.664
<i>♪ I wanna love somebody</i>

43:21.666 --> 43:23.700
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CHEERING)</font>

43:23.702 --> 43:25.635
<i>♪ I hear you need somebody</i>
<i>To love ♪</i>

43:25.637 --> 43:27.303
Whoo!

43:27.305 --> 43:28.972
Look at this! Yeah!

43:28.974 --> 43:30.940
<font color="#D900D9">(WHOOPING)</font>

