<font color="#808080">KIM:</font> Hey.
Hey.

01:04:43.513 --> 01:04:46.314
I was hoping I'd see you here.

01:04:47.917 --> 01:04:50.552
Um, we're doing a bonfire
down at the cove.

01:04:50.554 --> 01:04:52.120
You want to stop by after work?

01:04:52.122 --> 01:04:55.223
Oh, thanks, you know,
but I got to...

01:04:55.225 --> 01:04:57.259
<font color="#808080">BOY:</font>
Where's the action?

01:04:57.261 --> 01:04:59.361
I want to party!

01:04:59.363 --> 01:05:00.562
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CHUCKLE)</font>

01:05:03.199 --> 01:05:06.501
You know, come on.
I got a better idea.

01:05:06.503 --> 01:05:09.504
Yeah, okay, that's $14.56.

01:05:11.574 --> 01:05:13.975
Dude, no. What?

01:05:13.977 --> 01:05:15.610
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
I'll owe you forever, Blond.

01:05:15.612 --> 01:05:17.913
What's up?<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> I promise.

01:05:20.383 --> 01:05:24.686
Oh, hey.
Dude, you dropped your, uh...

01:05:40.169 --> 01:05:41.636
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CLOSES)</font>

01:05:43.039 --> 01:05:46.041
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> Hey.
You're home.

01:05:46.043 --> 01:05:49.244
Yeah, I finished up early,
so I thought I'd get back.

01:05:49.246 --> 01:05:50.545
Is Roque in her room?

01:05:50.547 --> 01:05:54.249
Yeah,
she's getting ready for bed.

01:05:54.251 --> 01:05:57.218
What's in the bag?
Oh.

01:05:57.220 --> 01:05:59.721
My old man used to read
to me as a kid,

01:05:59.723 --> 01:06:03.024
and I thought,
you know, maybe...

01:06:04.327 --> 01:06:07.162
Maybe I would start reading
to Roque.

01:06:08.431 --> 01:06:09.698
Okay.

01:06:16.038 --> 01:06:18.440
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCKING ON DOOR)</font><font color="#808080">
FROSTY:</font> Roque?

01:06:18.442 --> 01:06:20.175
<font color="#808080">ROQUE:</font>
Hi, Daddy.

01:06:20.177 --> 01:06:23.745
Hey, I take it this isn't
your first time here.

01:06:23.747 --> 01:06:26.414
It's my first time
with anyone else.

01:06:36.592 --> 01:06:38.560
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Look, you see that?

01:06:38.562 --> 01:06:41.529
That's the seventh brightest
star in the sky, Rigel.

01:06:41.531 --> 01:06:42.998
Right above it, on either side,

01:06:43.000 --> 01:06:44.599
that's Betelgeuse
and Bellatrix.

01:06:44.601 --> 01:06:46.301
It's the shoulders of Orion.

01:06:49.705 --> 01:06:51.606
What?
Ha, ha.

01:06:51.608 --> 01:06:53.408
How'd you know that?

01:06:53.410 --> 01:06:56.111
I learned it from my dad.

01:06:56.113 --> 01:06:57.746
He started teaching me
about the stars

01:06:57.748 --> 01:07:00.782
when I was maybe, like, 3 or 4.

01:07:00.784 --> 01:07:03.752
There are 88 constellations,

01:07:03.754 --> 01:07:06.388
but I never got a chance
to learn them all.

01:07:07.723 --> 01:07:11.493
<font color="#D900D9">(MAZZY STAR'S "FADE INTO YOU"
PLAYING)</font>

01:07:14.397 --> 01:07:16.231
Come on.

01:07:16.233 --> 01:07:17.632
Follow me.

01:07:19.301 --> 01:07:24.773
<i>♪ Fade into you</i>

01:07:26.675 --> 01:07:28.276
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font>
Whoa!

01:07:28.278 --> 01:07:30.812
<i>♪ Strange you never knew</i>

01:07:30.814 --> 01:07:34.382
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> Paddle, paddle, paddle!
Come on, Kimmy!

01:07:34.384 --> 01:07:36.117
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font>
Yeah!

01:07:36.119 --> 01:07:37.419
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Kimmy, give me your hand.

01:07:37.421 --> 01:07:39.521
Get over here.
Kimmy, come on. Come on.

01:07:39.523 --> 01:07:41.289
<font color="#D900D9">(KIM LAUGHS)</font>

01:07:41.291 --> 01:07:43.224
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> Ow!<font color="#808080">
KIM:</font> No!

01:07:45.294 --> 01:07:46.661
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

01:07:46.663 --> 01:07:51.599
<i>♪ Fade into you</i>

01:07:56.806 --> 01:07:58.706
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Frost, I saw you were counting

01:07:58.708 --> 01:08:01.176
on your fingers when we were
diving at Mavericks.

01:08:01.178 --> 01:08:04.679
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> The longer you're down
there, the more your mind unspools.

01:08:04.681 --> 01:08:08.683
You mark each minute
with a finger.

01:08:08.685 --> 01:08:10.752
Run out of fingers

01:08:10.754 --> 01:08:12.253
and you know you're in trouble.

01:08:18.694 --> 01:08:20.295
Feel the water getting colder?

01:08:20.296 --> 01:08:22.363
Yeah.

01:08:22.365 --> 01:08:24.332
Because of what lies
beneath us.

01:08:24.334 --> 01:08:28.303
It's the Monterey Trench,
5,280 feet deep.

01:08:28.305 --> 01:08:29.770
Current drops in here,

01:08:29.773 --> 01:08:33.274
heads east until it hits
the Southern Wall.

01:08:33.276 --> 01:08:35.877
Creating what?
It's a back eddy.

01:08:35.879 --> 01:08:37.578
You know,
the day you hit that eddy

01:08:37.581 --> 01:08:40.180
is the day you'll be
more than halfway there.

01:08:40.183 --> 01:08:41.749
Where'd you learn
all that stuff anyway?

01:08:41.751 --> 01:08:43.651
From you.

01:08:43.653 --> 01:08:45.520
I mean, from books and maps.

01:08:45.522 --> 01:08:47.455
You told me to study
the currents and the tides.

01:08:49.225 --> 01:08:50.425
Yeah, I guess I did, didn't I?

01:08:54.596 --> 01:08:56.731
Used to come out here

01:08:56.733 --> 01:08:59.134
and just paddle out
to the deepest part.

01:09:00.502 --> 01:09:02.904
Used to bob up and down
like a cork just...

01:09:02.906 --> 01:09:05.372
Just to feel it.

01:09:07.743 --> 01:09:10.411
To feel what?

01:09:10.412 --> 01:09:12.212
The abyss.

01:09:18.287 --> 01:09:21.421
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> The tide is
really strong today.

01:09:21.424 --> 01:09:25.260
That's because of
tropical hurricanes from Japan.

01:09:25.261 --> 01:09:27.362
Making their way
across the Pacific.

01:09:27.363 --> 01:09:28.729
Really?

01:09:28.732 --> 01:09:33.801
Only happens once
every seven to 10 years.

01:09:33.803 --> 01:09:37.372
Last El Niño was '83.

01:09:37.374 --> 01:09:38.840
Brought waves into Mavericks

01:09:38.841 --> 01:09:42.477
the size
of five-story buildings.

01:09:43.479 --> 01:09:46.214
Oh, yeah.
El Niño.

01:09:46.216 --> 01:09:48.448
Do you think it'll
happen again this year?

01:09:48.451 --> 01:09:50.785
I don't know.

01:09:50.787 --> 01:09:54.522
But if it does,
you'd better be ready.

01:09:55.524 --> 01:09:57.825
Because that wave of ours

01:09:57.827 --> 01:09:59.761
ain't gonna be
a secret anymore.

01:10:01.397 --> 01:10:03.264
<font color="#808080">GIRL 1:</font> So, girl I
want you to know

01:10:03.266 --> 01:10:07.669
♪ That wherever you go
I won't be far away ♪

01:10:07.671 --> 01:10:12.273
♪ Because as I kiss your lips
While you swing your hips ♪

01:10:12.275 --> 01:10:16.678
♪ You just see me say
She's my honey baby ♪

01:10:16.680 --> 01:10:18.413
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah

01:10:19.949 --> 01:10:21.583
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEERING)</font>

01:10:21.585 --> 01:10:22.817
<font color="#808080">GIRL 2:</font>
Nice.

01:10:22.819 --> 01:10:25.453
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Thank you, ladies.

01:10:25.455 --> 01:10:27.322
All right, I gotta
go get some wood.

01:10:27.324 --> 01:10:28.590
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font>
No.

01:10:28.592 --> 01:10:30.258
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
I got to keep you ladies warm.

01:10:30.260 --> 01:10:31.660
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font>
Why don't you go help Daddy?

01:10:31.661 --> 01:10:32.860
Bye.

01:10:32.862 --> 01:10:34.329
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font>
Oh, no. You're leaving.

01:10:34.331 --> 01:10:35.563
<font color="#808080">GIRL 1:</font>
Yeah, swing shift calls.

01:10:35.565 --> 01:10:39.801
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font>
No. Oh, good to see you.

01:10:42.638 --> 01:10:44.606
So, wait,
where did you guys meet?

01:10:44.608 --> 01:10:46.708
You're looking at it.
Really?

01:10:46.710 --> 01:10:50.378
Yeah. This is where we
went on our first date.

01:10:50.380 --> 01:10:53.481
He asked me out to dinner,
and before I know it,

01:10:53.483 --> 01:10:55.917
he's, you know, spearing a fish

01:10:55.919 --> 01:10:58.853
and cooking it over a campfire
like a caveman,

01:10:58.855 --> 01:11:00.455
and I'm just sitting there

01:11:00.457 --> 01:11:03.391
in my white taffeta dress
and my pearls,

01:11:03.393 --> 01:11:05.627
you know, wondering
where my cutlery is.

01:11:05.629 --> 01:11:07.328
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:11:09.732 --> 01:11:11.299
Is all of his family here?

01:11:11.301 --> 01:11:13.768
No, we're his only family.

01:11:13.770 --> 01:11:16.738
Frosty lost both his folks
when he was young.

01:11:16.740 --> 01:11:18.373
He doesn't really
talk about it much.

01:11:18.375 --> 01:11:20.375
Kind of carries it
on the inside.

01:11:20.377 --> 01:11:22.577
Always has.

01:11:22.579 --> 01:11:25.046
Somehow,

01:11:26.882 --> 01:11:30.752
it's just made him feel
unfit. Hey.

01:11:30.754 --> 01:11:32.987
I don't know. It just...
It breaks my heart.

01:11:40.596 --> 01:11:42.897
You take care of that boy,
you hear?

01:11:44.066 --> 01:11:45.900
Yeah, I will.
Okay.

01:11:45.902 --> 01:11:48.036
I mean, we're just friends,
but I'll take care of him.

01:11:48.038 --> 01:11:50.371
Just friends?<font color="#808080">
JAY:</font> Hey, hey.

01:11:50.373 --> 01:11:52.473
<font color="#808080">KIM:</font> Wow. Nice catch!
Anybody want to kiss a fish?

01:11:52.475 --> 01:11:54.776
Not me.
Eh? Yeah.

01:11:54.778 --> 01:11:56.077
No! No! Jay, no!

01:11:56.079 --> 01:11:58.379
No! Do not get that
near me! No!

01:11:58.381 --> 01:11:59.781
No!

01:11:59.783 --> 01:12:01.015
<font color="#D900D9">(JAY SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:12:01.017 --> 01:12:03.351
<font color="#D900D9">(KIM SHRIEKING)</font>

01:12:03.353 --> 01:12:05.353
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

01:12:07.456 --> 01:12:09.691
Hey.

01:12:09.693 --> 01:12:12.794
<font color="#808080">GIRL:</font>
What's up? Hey. How are you?

01:12:27.543 --> 01:12:29.444
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOND & BELLS LAUGHING)</font>

01:12:30.546 --> 01:12:33.681
Oh...<font color="#808080">
SONNY:</font> Well, well.

01:12:33.683 --> 01:12:35.550
Glad you showed up.

01:12:35.552 --> 01:12:38.052
We came to see
the Mavericks man.

01:12:41.590 --> 01:12:43.858
What are they doing here?

01:12:43.860 --> 01:12:45.693
What are you, like,
Neighborhood Watch?

01:12:45.695 --> 01:12:47.562
<font color="#808080">SONNY:</font> So, what's the
deal, little trash?

01:12:47.564 --> 01:12:50.131
You gonna slay
that dragon by yourself

01:12:50.133 --> 01:12:51.933
or is your
rent-a-dad gonna help?

01:12:55.838 --> 01:12:57.805
<font color="#D900D9">(SONNY CLEARS THROAT)</font>

01:12:57.807 --> 01:13:00.441
"From a distance,
I watched and realized

01:13:00.443 --> 01:13:04.479
"that along with rare beauty
comes constant scrutiny.

01:13:04.481 --> 01:13:07.749
Like being the lead
in a school play."

01:13:07.751 --> 01:13:09.650
<font color="#D900D9">(BOY LAUGHS AND CLAPS)</font>

01:13:11.086 --> 01:13:12.854
That's poetic, man.

01:13:15.524 --> 01:13:18.493
It's a shame she laughs at you
behind your back, though.

01:13:18.495 --> 01:13:20.762
But, I mean, you already
knew that, right?

01:13:20.764 --> 01:13:22.930
It's kind of obvious since
she won't be seen with you.

01:13:35.844 --> 01:13:39.514
Paddle, paddle, paddle,
little grom.

01:13:39.516 --> 01:13:41.649
Paddle, paddle, paddle.

01:13:41.651 --> 01:13:44.652
♪♪♪

01:14:17.953 --> 01:14:19.987
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
I'm not doing it again.

01:14:21.890 --> 01:14:25.793
Okay, well, you know the deal.

01:14:25.795 --> 01:14:28.529
You want to walk,
that's your choice.

01:14:28.531 --> 01:14:29.897
Why are you doing this to me?

01:14:29.899 --> 01:14:31.699
Because I want the truth.

01:14:33.068 --> 01:14:34.669
I want to know
what you're afraid of.

01:14:37.606 --> 01:14:38.973
I don't know.

01:14:38.975 --> 01:14:41.075
You don't know?
Or you don't wanna know?

01:14:41.077 --> 01:14:42.677
I don't know.

01:14:42.679 --> 01:14:45.780
Well, you better ask yourself,

01:14:45.782 --> 01:14:47.982
what do you want
to leave behind?

01:14:47.984 --> 01:14:51.953
The truth of who you really are
or just some words on a page?

01:14:51.955 --> 01:14:54.856
All that stuff that's burning
deep down inside of you,

01:14:54.858 --> 01:14:56.557
what is that?

01:14:56.559 --> 01:14:57.992
That stuff
you can't even look at

01:14:57.994 --> 01:14:59.594
because it scares you so much,

01:14:59.596 --> 01:15:01.662
that the same thing
in that letter?

01:15:01.664 --> 01:15:03.231
That letter
that you can't open...

01:15:03.233 --> 01:15:04.732
Don't.
But you can't even throw away.

01:15:04.734 --> 01:15:06.734
Don't do this!
Don't do what?

01:15:06.736 --> 01:15:08.870
If you don't even have
the courage

01:15:08.872 --> 01:15:10.271
to open that letter,

01:15:10.273 --> 01:15:12.073
then how can you
take on that wave?

01:15:12.075 --> 01:15:15.576
Stop it! I don't know, okay?
I said I don't know.

01:15:15.578 --> 01:15:16.811
<font color="#D900D9">(CLATTERING THEN THUDDING)</font>

01:15:16.813 --> 01:15:18.079
<font color="#D900D9">(ROQUE SCREAMS)</font>

01:15:20.082 --> 01:15:21.949
Dad, quick, Mommy's sick.

01:15:27.122 --> 01:15:28.856
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Brenda.

01:15:28.858 --> 01:15:30.992
<font color="#808080">ROQUE:</font>
Mommy?

01:15:30.994 --> 01:15:34.562
Jay. Call 911.
I'm here, sweetheart.

01:15:34.564 --> 01:15:36.597
I'm right here. Hurry.

01:15:36.599 --> 01:15:39.267
Mommy. Mommy!

01:15:39.269 --> 01:15:40.902
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> Yeah, yeah, we
have an emergency.

01:15:40.904 --> 01:15:42.236
Babe, I'm with you.

01:15:42.238 --> 01:15:44.005
I need you
to send an ambulance, please.

01:15:44.007 --> 01:15:45.840
Jay, tell them
she's having a stroke.

01:15:45.842 --> 01:15:47.575
I think she's having
a stroke. She can't talk.

01:15:47.577 --> 01:15:49.277
Just breathe, baby.

01:15:49.279 --> 01:15:50.845
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> I don't know. I don't know.
She fell...

01:15:50.847 --> 01:15:52.747
Mommy! Mommy!

01:15:52.749 --> 01:15:54.015
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
She's not moving.

01:15:55.684 --> 01:15:57.552
Okay, babe. Baby, I got you.

01:15:57.554 --> 01:16:01.556
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> We're at 311 38th
Street, in Pleasant Point.

01:16:10.299 --> 01:16:13.100
<font color="#D900D9">(ORGAN PLAYING HYMN)</font>

01:16:27.349 --> 01:16:29.750
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
Hi.

01:16:29.752 --> 01:16:31.052
How could this happen?

01:16:34.690 --> 01:16:36.757
Jay, can we talk?

01:16:36.759 --> 01:16:38.926
Please?

01:16:38.928 --> 01:16:40.161
Are you okay?

01:16:40.163 --> 01:16:42.029
No.

01:16:43.932 --> 01:16:45.633
I have to go.

01:16:45.635 --> 01:16:48.002
Okay.

01:16:48.004 --> 01:16:50.004
<font color="#D900D9">(JAY SNIFFLING)</font>

01:16:57.079 --> 01:16:59.914
♪♪♪

01:17:08.090 --> 01:17:09.757
Go away.

01:17:27.075 --> 01:17:30.411
My grandchildren are wondering
where their father is.

01:17:32.147 --> 01:17:34.982
No, they're wondering
where their mother is, sir.

01:17:34.984 --> 01:17:36.717
Then tell them.

01:17:38.353 --> 01:17:39.987
I don't know what to say.

01:17:39.989 --> 01:17:42.056
Tell them the truth.

01:17:42.058 --> 01:17:43.858
She's at the side of God
in heaven.

01:17:43.860 --> 01:17:45.993
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

01:17:45.995 --> 01:17:49.263
Well, I'm not sure
I believe that right now.

01:17:56.004 --> 01:17:57.438
Maybe...

01:17:59.141 --> 01:18:01.409
Maybe we'll take the kids
for a couple of days.

01:18:05.313 --> 01:18:06.814
Yeah.

01:18:08.183 --> 01:18:10.785
Those two children
have lost their mother.

01:18:12.220 --> 01:18:16.157
Now don't deny them
the comfort of their father.

01:18:16.159 --> 01:18:18.292
Now, come inside.

01:18:22.297 --> 01:18:25.066
♪♪♪

01:18:50.759 --> 01:18:52.927
Why did he leave us, Mom?

01:19:00.001 --> 01:19:02.203
He didn't leave us.

01:19:02.205 --> 01:19:04.138
He left me.

01:19:15.283 --> 01:19:17.852
Frosty?

01:19:17.854 --> 01:19:19.353
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCKING ON DOOR)</font>

01:19:19.355 --> 01:19:21.388
Frost.

01:19:21.390 --> 01:19:23.824
Hey, Frosty?

01:19:28.497 --> 01:19:31.265
<font color="#808080">BRENDA:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON TV)</font> <i>Show Daddy
the soft baby rabbit.</i>

01:19:31.267 --> 01:19:32.800
<i>Say, "Hi."</i>

01:19:32.802 --> 01:19:35.102
<i>Say, "I love you, Daddy."</i>

01:19:35.104 --> 01:19:36.971
<font color="#D900D9">(BRENDA LAUGHING ON TV)</font>

01:19:38.907 --> 01:19:40.274
<i>Can you show Daddy?</i>

01:19:40.276 --> 01:19:41.976
<i>Show Daddy</i>
<i>the soft baby rabbit.</i>

01:19:41.978 --> 01:19:43.978
<i>Say, "Hi." Can you say,</i>
<i>"I love you, Daddy."</i>

01:19:43.980 --> 01:19:45.212
Frost?

01:19:45.214 --> 01:19:47.515
<i>Hi, Daddy. She said, "Da!"</i>

01:19:47.517 --> 01:19:49.383
<i>She said "Daddy."</i>

01:19:49.385 --> 01:19:52.286
<i>That's good. Should we read</i>
<i>a story to Daddy?</i>

01:19:52.288 --> 01:19:54.255
<i>Should we read a story...</i>

01:19:54.257 --> 01:19:57.958
♪♪♪

01:20:03.131 --> 01:20:04.431
Deep breaths.

01:20:04.433 --> 01:20:06.567
Steady rhythm.

01:20:06.569 --> 01:20:08.869
Drive and glide.

01:20:16.945 --> 01:20:18.946
Frosty!

01:20:27.823 --> 01:20:29.123
Deep breaths.

01:20:29.125 --> 01:20:30.558
Steady rhythm.

01:20:30.560 --> 01:20:32.259
Drive and glide.

01:20:34.462 --> 01:20:37.464
Frosty!

01:20:37.466 --> 01:20:39.900
Frosty!

01:20:56.151 --> 01:20:58.919
The current.

01:20:58.921 --> 01:21:00.221
He floated with the current.

01:21:00.223 --> 01:21:00.723
♪♪♪

01:21:21.209 --> 01:21:24.044
Frosty, what are you doing?
What are you doing?

01:21:24.046 --> 01:21:26.580
You can't just
walk away from everything!

01:21:26.582 --> 01:21:30.050
Why not? Huh? Why not?

01:21:36.925 --> 01:21:39.460
She's all I had, Jay.

01:21:39.462 --> 01:21:41.295
She's all I ever knew.

01:21:43.431 --> 01:21:45.199
All I know, Frost,
is what you told me.

01:21:45.201 --> 01:21:47.368
If you look hard enough,

01:21:47.370 --> 01:21:49.904
there's always a way
through it.

01:21:49.906 --> 01:21:51.639
But what if I don't
have the strength, Jay?

01:21:54.609 --> 01:21:56.577
Which pillar do I lean on then?

01:21:58.246 --> 01:21:59.480
The fifth one.

01:22:01.249 --> 01:22:02.516
Which one is that?

01:22:02.518 --> 01:22:04.618
It's me.

01:22:07.122 --> 01:22:09.423
Come on.

01:22:09.425 --> 01:22:10.658
That's enough of this.

01:22:12.327 --> 01:22:14.662
Come on. It's time to go.

01:22:16.998 --> 01:22:18.432
Hey, Jay.

01:22:18.434 --> 01:22:20.401
You're going the wrong way.

01:22:20.403 --> 01:22:23.270
I felt the back eddy, Frost.

01:22:23.272 --> 01:22:25.372
That means we're more than
halfway across the bay.

01:22:25.374 --> 01:22:27.541
Closer to what's in front of us
than what's behind.

01:22:37.018 --> 01:22:38.385
Paddle, Frosty.

01:22:41.656 --> 01:22:45.392
♪♪♪

01:23:12.220 --> 01:23:14.021
<font color="#D900D9">(JAY GRUNTS)</font>

01:23:14.023 --> 01:23:15.689
Good morning.

01:23:18.526 --> 01:23:20.594
Did you forget what day it is?

01:23:23.331 --> 01:23:27.067
Oh. And this
is all of the money

01:23:27.069 --> 01:23:28.402
that I borrowed from you.

01:23:29.604 --> 01:23:31.472
Plus some interest.

01:23:37.412 --> 01:23:39.513
Mom, where did you get this?

01:23:39.515 --> 01:23:42.116
I was made the shift manager
because I'm so punctual.

01:23:46.488 --> 01:23:49.356
All right.
Open your present.

01:23:52.093 --> 01:23:53.494
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:24:00.702 --> 01:24:02.636
Frosty said that
you might be needing that

01:24:02.638 --> 01:24:04.505
to follow the swells.

01:24:06.775 --> 01:24:10.811
And he said there is
a very big one coming.

01:24:10.813 --> 01:24:13.747
It was hard to figure out what
he was talking about,

01:24:13.749 --> 01:24:17.451
but they're calling it El Niño,
which means "the boy."

01:24:19.120 --> 01:24:23.057
You know that because
you got a C in Spanish. Hey.

01:24:23.059 --> 01:24:25.125
You knew about this
the whole time.

01:24:26.261 --> 01:24:27.661
Yeah. Frosty's no dummy,

01:24:27.663 --> 01:24:30.664
and my handwriting
is not that good.

01:24:36.504 --> 01:24:39.239
♪♪♪

01:24:43.244 --> 01:24:44.778
Happy birthday.

01:25:14.709 --> 01:25:17.644
Yes! Ha!

01:25:21.583 --> 01:25:24.418
Nice weather we're having,
eh, ladies?

01:25:24.420 --> 01:25:26.286
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Hey. How's it going, Bob?

01:25:26.288 --> 01:25:27.721
How you holding up?

01:25:27.723 --> 01:25:29.857
Yeah, yeah. Good.

01:25:31.159 --> 01:25:32.359
This is Jay.

01:25:32.361 --> 01:25:34.595
Bob Pearson.
Heard a lot about you, kid.

01:25:34.597 --> 01:25:37.731
Thank you, sir.
Follow me.

01:25:37.733 --> 01:25:39.600
How's it cooking?
Catching any waves?

01:25:39.602 --> 01:25:41.468
No, I'll never surf anymore.

01:25:41.470 --> 01:25:43.804
I'm making too many boards
for all you guys.

01:25:43.806 --> 01:25:46.240
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font> That's the way
I like to keep it.

01:25:51.479 --> 01:25:55.482
You want to slay a giant,
you need a sacred spear.

01:25:55.484 --> 01:25:58.552
Happy birthday, Jay.

01:26:02.223 --> 01:26:04.191
Can I...?

01:26:04.193 --> 01:26:05.692
Yeah. She's all yours.

01:26:08.596 --> 01:26:11.632
♪♪♪

01:26:19.607 --> 01:26:20.874
I don't know what to say.

01:26:20.876 --> 01:26:23.477
Just stay low, go fast.

01:26:23.479 --> 01:26:25.212
Yeah. Yeah.

01:26:26.514 --> 01:26:27.014
♪♪♪

01:26:42.897 --> 01:26:45.265
There. There he is.

01:26:56.311 --> 01:26:58.412
Yeah, he can take a beating.

01:26:58.414 --> 01:27:00.647
But can he surf?

01:27:00.649 --> 01:27:02.416
Like nothing you've ever seen.

01:27:05.353 --> 01:27:07.554
You ever seen anyone that can
tread water like that

01:27:07.556 --> 01:27:09.556
for 45 minutes
without drowning?

01:27:13.728 --> 01:27:16.830
He's got a point.

01:27:16.832 --> 01:27:19.666
Good, I'll take that
as two yeses.

01:27:25.607 --> 01:27:27.975
Just make sure he doesn't
drop in on me, all right?

01:27:29.844 --> 01:27:32.412
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font> <i>Strong El
Niño induced winter storms</i>

01:27:32.414 --> 01:27:34.314
<i>are queued up</i>
<i>in the Gulf of Alaska</i>

01:27:34.316 --> 01:27:36.550
<i>and progressing eastward</i>
<i>towards California.</i>

01:27:36.552 --> 01:27:40.454
The first is producing 55-knot
<i>winds and seas to 40 feet.</i>

01:27:40.456 --> 01:27:42.823
<i>Large ocean swells</i>
<i>are expected to arrive</i>

01:27:42.825 --> 01:27:44.324
<font color="#D900D9">(RAISES VOLUME ON RADIO)</font>

01:27:44.326 --> 01:27:45.892
<i>resulting in large</i>
<i>breaking waves</i>

01:27:45.894 --> 01:27:48.595
<i>with heights to 35 feet.</i>
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCKING CONTINUES)</font>

01:27:54.902 --> 01:27:57.471
Hey. It's pouring out there.

01:28:01.743 --> 01:28:02.943
How you been?

01:28:04.545 --> 01:28:05.746
Good.

01:28:12.020 --> 01:28:16.356
Kim, what's wrong?

01:28:18.026 --> 01:28:19.559
We've been friends forever.

01:28:19.561 --> 01:28:21.028
You don't have to do this.
Just tell me.

01:28:21.030 --> 01:28:24.364
It's just complicated.

01:28:24.366 --> 01:28:25.866
Not from where I'm sitting.

01:28:28.002 --> 01:28:30.337
That's because you only see
the good in everything.

01:28:31.806 --> 01:28:34.007
Most of us spend
all of our time

01:28:34.009 --> 01:28:36.576
dwelling on all the what ifs

01:28:36.578 --> 01:28:38.445
and just looking for
all the reasons

01:28:38.447 --> 01:28:40.814
why things
could never work out.

01:28:40.816 --> 01:28:42.516
And what if you're wrong?

01:28:44.519 --> 01:28:47.954
Then you show up
to a pizza parlor

01:28:47.956 --> 01:28:49.723
late one night, in the rain.

01:28:54.662 --> 01:28:58.365
Ever since we were
little kids, Jay,

01:29:00.068 --> 01:29:03.670
I've just had this feeling
deep down inside...

01:29:05.506 --> 01:29:06.940
...that you're the one,

01:29:06.942 --> 01:29:10.610
and I'm gonna spend
the rest of my life with you.

01:29:13.815 --> 01:29:15.349
What?

01:29:16.918 --> 01:29:18.652
What's wrong?

01:29:26.828 --> 01:29:29.496
♪♪♪

01:30:45.807 --> 01:30:47.707
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font>
<i>Be advised,</i>

01:30:47.709 --> 01:30:49.509
<i>there is an extremely high</i>
<i>surf advisory in effect.</i>

01:30:49.511 --> 01:30:51.945
<i>Buoys reporting</i>
<i>32 feet at 18 seconds.</i>

01:30:51.947 --> 01:30:53.747
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

01:30:56.217 --> 01:30:57.651
Hey.

01:30:57.653 --> 01:31:01.788
Hey, Frosty, I just heard,
32 at 18.

01:31:03.090 --> 01:31:04.858
Okay.

01:31:04.860 --> 01:31:06.793
Okay, I'll call Kim.

01:31:13.835 --> 01:31:15.168
Are you sure
you don't wanna come?

01:31:16.537 --> 01:31:18.672
I just want you to come home.

01:31:23.678 --> 01:31:24.945
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
You sure you got everything?

01:31:24.947 --> 01:31:27.080
Yeah.

01:31:28.683 --> 01:31:30.984
All right, then.
Because of that,

01:31:30.986 --> 01:31:32.786
there'll be a lot of cowboys
out there today

01:31:32.788 --> 01:31:34.554
trying to prove themselves.

01:31:34.556 --> 01:31:36.890
Some of them
are gonna get hurt.

01:31:36.892 --> 01:31:40.894
So keep your distance
and keep your focus, all right?

01:31:47.735 --> 01:31:51.671
So a swell with this much west

01:31:51.673 --> 01:31:53.206
means sets will be shifting.

01:31:55.076 --> 01:31:56.910
So you better be prepared.

01:31:59.947 --> 01:32:02.749
Pull over. Pull over.

01:32:07.054 --> 01:32:09.055
<font color="#D900D9">(RETCHING AND COUGHING)</font>

01:32:11.859 --> 01:32:14.661
♪♪♪

01:32:24.705 --> 01:32:26.706
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

01:32:35.750 --> 01:32:37.884
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
Let's keep you warm, okay?

01:32:37.886 --> 01:32:39.886
Okay.
All right.

01:32:45.726 --> 01:32:47.327
I'll catch up with you.

01:32:48.930 --> 01:32:50.830
Hey.
Hey.

01:32:51.832 --> 01:32:54.167
Coast looks pretty scary.

01:32:54.169 --> 01:32:56.703
Never seen it this big before.

01:32:59.273 --> 01:33:01.308
I've been thinking
about a lot of things lately.

01:33:02.643 --> 01:33:04.177
You taught me to surf.

01:33:04.179 --> 01:33:06.646
I never thanked you for that.

01:33:08.583 --> 01:33:10.116
I'll be watching you, man.

01:33:17.825 --> 01:33:21.294
<font color="#D900D9">(BOYS CHEERING)</font>

01:33:22.797 --> 01:33:25.599
End of an innocence,
my brother.

01:33:30.838 --> 01:33:32.305
How you feeling, kid?

01:33:32.307 --> 01:33:34.140
You ready?

01:33:34.142 --> 01:33:36.910
Suit up.
We'll paddle out together.

01:33:39.347 --> 01:33:41.314
What about you, Frost?

01:33:41.316 --> 01:33:43.984
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:33:43.986 --> 01:33:46.953
I made a promise
a long time ago, chief.

01:33:58.332 --> 01:34:00.867
That isn't El Niño, boys.

01:34:00.869 --> 01:34:03.103
That's El Jefe right there.

01:34:06.107 --> 01:34:08.074
You gotta be kidding me.

01:34:09.810 --> 01:34:11.945
It's too big for the kid.

01:34:21.756 --> 01:34:23.156
Jay, are you sure about this?

01:34:23.158 --> 01:34:26.126
I mean, really, really sure?

01:34:26.128 --> 01:34:27.694
Because I'm not.

01:34:33.034 --> 01:34:34.267
I am.

01:34:47.415 --> 01:34:51.084
I know what you're
gonna say, so don't.

01:34:51.086 --> 01:34:53.053
That wasn't the deal.

01:34:53.055 --> 01:34:54.287
Remember?

01:34:54.289 --> 01:34:56.756
No questions, no arguing.

01:35:03.297 --> 01:35:04.998
I just wanted to tell you
something

01:35:05.000 --> 01:35:07.133
I should've told you long ago.

01:35:08.769 --> 01:35:10.870
Which is, it doesn't matter.

01:35:10.872 --> 01:35:15.875
Whether you decide to
paddle out or take that drop,

01:35:17.378 --> 01:35:20.046
I love you no matter what.

01:35:26.454 --> 01:35:28.154
Frost.

01:35:49.910 --> 01:35:51.277
Come on.

01:36:00.488 --> 01:36:03.923
♪♪♪

01:36:32.219 --> 01:36:35.789
Hey, get us closer! Closer!

01:36:46.834 --> 01:36:49.836
♪♪♪

01:36:57.444 --> 01:36:58.978
Let's do it!

01:36:58.980 --> 01:37:01.281
<font color="#808080">MAN 1:</font> Whoo!<font color="#808080">
MAN 2:</font> Go time!

01:37:09.423 --> 01:37:13.259
♪♪♪

01:37:51.866 --> 01:37:53.199
Ah...

01:37:56.503 --> 01:37:59.572
♪♪♪

01:38:04.879 --> 01:38:06.613
Get out of here!
Sets are shifting!

01:38:08.082 --> 01:38:10.183
Swing wide! Outside!

01:38:10.185 --> 01:38:11.625
<font color="#808080">MAN 3:</font>
Kid, paddle, paddle, paddle!

01:38:15.289 --> 01:38:16.489
<font color="#808080">MAN 4:</font>
Go, go, go!

01:38:18.225 --> 01:38:21.628
♪♪♪

01:38:29.370 --> 01:38:30.610
Get your boats out of here now!

01:38:33.507 --> 01:38:37.110
♪♪♪

01:38:45.119 --> 01:38:46.953
<font color="#808080">MAN 4:</font>
Go, Jay, get out!

01:38:46.955 --> 01:38:49.255
<font color="#808080">MAN 3:</font>
Paddle, paddle, paddle!

01:38:52.259 --> 01:38:54.961
♪♪♪

01:39:02.670 --> 01:39:05.204
Somebody's gonna die out there.

01:39:13.681 --> 01:39:15.682
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN 5 SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

01:39:22.389 --> 01:39:26.159
♪♪♪

01:39:43.277 --> 01:39:45.578
♪♪♪

01:40:16.477 --> 01:40:18.478
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)</font>

01:40:49.743 --> 01:40:53.246
♪♪♪

01:41:04.725 --> 01:41:06.526
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
He'll be okay,

01:41:06.528 --> 01:41:08.528
as long as he can still
climb up the leash.

01:41:08.530 --> 01:41:10.797
♪♪♪

01:41:29.850 --> 01:41:31.417
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

01:41:39.326 --> 01:41:42.695
♪♪♪

01:41:56.310 --> 01:41:57.677
<font color="#808080">FROST:</font>
Come on, Jay.

01:41:59.880 --> 01:42:02.682
♪♪♪

01:42:10.591 --> 01:42:13.392
Come on, Jay.

01:42:20.834 --> 01:42:22.435
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:42:24.638 --> 01:42:27.874
♪♪♪

01:42:27.876 --> 01:42:30.309
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

01:42:31.445 --> 01:42:32.745
There he is!

01:42:32.747 --> 01:42:36.449
♪♪♪

01:43:00.674 --> 01:43:01.908
Grab ahold!

01:43:01.910 --> 01:43:05.311
No, no, no! Give me my board!

01:43:07.514 --> 01:43:09.682
You heard him!

01:43:15.489 --> 01:43:16.923
Thanks.

01:43:23.263 --> 01:43:24.664
Wait a minute.
What's he doing?

01:43:32.573 --> 01:43:34.941
He came to surf Mavericks.

01:43:37.277 --> 01:43:40.313
<font color="#808080">MAN 6:</font>
Set it up, man. Set it up.

01:43:40.315 --> 01:43:42.215
<font color="#808080">MAN 7:</font> Take it.<font color="#808080">
MAN 8:</font> I got it.

01:43:42.217 --> 01:43:43.416
<font color="#808080">MAN 7:</font>
Thanks.

01:43:43.418 --> 01:43:45.418
<font color="#808080">MAN 9:</font>
Hold on, hold on.

01:43:46.420 --> 01:43:48.421
Got it?<font color="#808080">
MAN 7:</font> Yeah.

01:43:53.460 --> 01:43:56.796
♪♪♪

01:44:08.842 --> 01:44:11.711
Come on, man,
you don't have to surf it.

01:44:11.713 --> 01:44:13.512
Came this far,
you at least need to feel it.

01:44:13.514 --> 01:44:16.249
No.

01:44:16.251 --> 01:44:18.384
Think I've felt enough
for one day.

01:44:24.791 --> 01:44:26.726
Kill it.

01:44:36.270 --> 01:44:39.338
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
<i>Dear Frosty,</i>

01:44:39.340 --> 01:44:41.641
<i>Truth is that I am afraid.</i>

01:44:41.643 --> 01:44:43.476
<i>I'm afraid I'll never</i>
<i>see my dad again</i>

01:44:43.478 --> 01:44:45.578
<i>and that my mom</i>
<i>will never find happiness.</i>

01:44:47.014 --> 01:44:48.881
<i>I'm afraid of losing Kim</i>

01:44:48.883 --> 01:44:51.384
<i>because she's the love</i>
<i>of my life.</i>

01:44:51.386 --> 01:44:55.021
<i>And, of course,</i>
<i>I'm afraid of losing you.</i>

01:44:55.023 --> 01:44:57.490
<i>I'm not sure what you think</i>
<i>fathers are supposed to be,</i>

01:44:57.492 --> 01:44:59.992
<i>but now I know</i>
<i>what they should be.</i>

01:45:05.699 --> 01:45:08.768
Glad to see you made it, kid.

01:45:08.770 --> 01:45:10.770
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font> <i>I finally read
my dad's letter,</i>

01:45:10.772 --> 01:45:13.639
<i>which was like</i>
<i>my last essay to you.</i>

01:45:13.641 --> 01:45:14.974
<i>Just a bunch of words</i>
<i>on a page.</i>

01:45:17.344 --> 01:45:20.012
♪♪♪

01:45:31.425 --> 01:45:33.092
This one's all you, charger.

01:45:33.094 --> 01:45:35.061
<font color="#808080">JAY:</font>
<i>I know this sounds strange,</i>

01:45:35.063 --> 01:45:36.762
<i>but I've always felt</i>

01:45:36.764 --> 01:45:38.698
<i>like I wouldn't be around</i>
<i>for very long,</i>

01:45:38.700 --> 01:45:41.434
<i>which is why</i>
<i>I want to take that drop.</i>

01:45:41.436 --> 01:45:44.103
<i>Because once I look down</i>
<i>over the edge</i>

01:45:44.105 --> 01:45:46.105
<i>and I catch it,</i>
<i>I'll become a part of it.</i>

01:45:48.041 --> 01:45:50.943
<i>And in that moment,</i>
<i>I'll know that I'm alive.</i>

01:45:50.945 --> 01:45:54.380
♪♪♪

01:46:42.462 --> 01:46:44.463
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEERING)</font>

01:46:48.835 --> 01:46:51.871
♪♪♪

01:47:52.065 --> 01:47:53.933
<font color="#808080">FROSTY:</font>
<i>Jay became famous that day,</i>

01:47:53.935 --> 01:47:55.868
<i>not for riding giants,</i>

01:47:55.870 --> 01:47:59.705
<i>but for the courage of a boy</i>
<i>who dared the impossible.</i>

01:47:59.707 --> 01:48:02.508
<i>Over the years, he rose to</i>
<i>the peak of the surfing world,</i>

01:48:02.510 --> 01:48:05.911
<i>his prowess matched</i>
<i>only by his joy.</i>

01:48:05.913 --> 01:48:08.881
<i>The true prince</i>
<i>amidst a sport of kings.</i>

01:48:08.883 --> 01:48:10.749
<i>He married</i>
<i>his childhood sweetheart</i>

01:48:10.751 --> 01:48:12.818
<i>and swore himself true.</i>

01:48:15.555 --> 01:48:18.557
♪♪♪

01:48:28.568 --> 01:48:30.703
<i>As for the rest,</i>

01:48:34.541 --> 01:48:38.110
<i>all I will say is, the ones</i>
<i>who push the limits discover...</i>

01:48:40.046 --> 01:48:43.048
<i>...the limits sometimes</i>
<i>push back.</i>

01:49:03.136 --> 01:49:06.272
♪♪♪

01:49:26.726 --> 01:49:28.160
To Jay!

01:49:35.302 --> 01:49:37.703
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font>
To Jay!

01:49:38.939 --> 01:49:42.174
To Jay!
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEERING)</font>

01:49:42.176 --> 01:49:44.610
Yeah!

